<IMG SRC="/web/images/pstaricn.gif" align="left"><H1>General References of interest in Medicine</H1><BR CLEAR=ALL>

Here are some interesting resources:
<UL>
<LI>The <A HREF="http://www.pitt.edu/HOME/GHNet/GHNet.html">Global Health Network</A>: an extensive review of many health resources.
<LI>the <A HREF="http://debra.dgbt.doc.ca/~mike/home.html">HealthNet Projects Home Page</A> created by the Communications Development Directorate of Industry Canada
<LI><A HREF="http://indy.radiology.uiowa.edu/VirtualHospital.html">The Virtual Hospital</A>: The University of Iowa's medical multimedia database that includes CME courses, patient simulations, etc.
<LI>The <A HREF="http://www.nih.gov/">National Institutes of Health</A> (NIH) Home Page: which contains information about grants, research oportunities, and more
<LI><A HREF="http://cancer.med.upenn.edu/">OncoLink</A> - the University of Pennsylvania's award winning oncology resource
<LI><A HREF="http://musom.mu.wvnet.edu/0u:/peds/poi.htm|">Points of Pediatric Interest</A>: an excellent overview of links to organizations, parenting resources, hospitals, etc. maintained by Christoph U. Lehmann, M.D. at the <A HREF="http://musom.mu.wvnet.edu/0u:/peds/general.htm| ">Marshal University Department of Pediatrics</A> at the <A HREF="http://musom.mu.wvnet.edu/">Marshall University School of Medicine</A>.
<LI>The <A HREF="http://www.bmj.com/bmj/">British Medical Journal</A>
<LI>The Uniformed Services University of the Health Sciences <A HREF="http://wwwpath.usuf2.usuhs.mil/default.html">(USUHS) Department of Pathology</A> which provided monthly cases on line for CME credit.
</UL>
<P>
There are several medical centers on the Web:
<UL>
<LI>The <A HREF="http://www.med.umich.edu/">University of Michigan Hospitals</A>
<LI>The <A HREF="http://www.mc.duke.edu/">Duke University</A> Medical Center
<LI>The <A HREF="http://med-www.stanford.edu/">Stanford University</A> Medical Center
</UL>
