<HEAD>
<TITLE>Software for the Web</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#EEFFFF">
<B><A HREF="/">Home</A> | <A HREF="./">Up</A> | <A HREF="/web/tools/">Tools</A> | <A HREF="/web/scripts/comment.acgi">Send a comment</A></B>
<HR>
<IMG SRC="http://www.psych.med.umich.edu/web/images/pstaricn.gif" align="left"><h1>Macintosh Software for the Web</h1>
This is a page of Macintosh based software for the Web.  We plan to add a page for Windows based software when we get time.  Software categories are based on use.
<HR>
<H2>Browsers</H2>
Browsers are software that let you examine the World Wide Web.  Different browsers have different features and may therefore display the same page differently.
<UL>
<LI><a href="http://home.netscape.com/comprod/mirror/index.html">Netscape</a> from the Netscape company: this is our recommended browser as it is the most popular one on the Internet.
<LI>Mosaic: free software from the NCSA
<LI>MacWeb
</UL>
<HR>
<H2>Helper Applications</H2>
Helper Applications are software that work with your browser to allow you to handle unusual file types when your browser encounters them.
<UL>
<LI><B>JPEGView</B>: for handling gif, jpeg, tiff, and other graphics files (<A HREF="gopher://gopher.archive.umich.edu:7055/40/mac/graphics/graphicsutil/jpegview3.31.sit.hqx">download</A> 774K)
<LI><B>SoundMachine</B>: for handling au, snd, aiff, and other sound files (<A HREF="gopher://gopher.archive.umich.edu:7055/40/mac/sound/soundutil/soundmachine2.1.cpt.hqx">download</A> 75K)
<LI><B>MoviePlayer</B>: for handling QuickTime files
<LI><B>Sparkle</B>: for handling mpeg files (<A HREF="gopher://gopher.archive.umich.edu:7055/40/mac/graphics/graphicsutil/sparkle2.45.sit.hqx">download</A> 1110K)
<LI><B>AVI to QT Utility</B>: for handling avi files
<LI><B>Stuffit Expander</B>: for decompressing hqx, sit files (<A HREF="ftp://grind.isca.uiowa.edu/mac/infomac/_Compress-%26_Translate/stuffit-
expander-352.sea">download</A> 186K)
<LI><B>ZipIt</B>: for decompressing zip, gz, tgz files
</UL>
<HR>
<H2>HTML Editors</H2>
HTML Editors are software that help you create files in HTML.
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://dragon.acadiau.ca/~giles/HTML_Editor/Documentation.html">HTML Editor for the Macintosh</A>: shareware semi-WYSIWYG page editor
<LI><A HREF="http://www.student.potsdam.edu/web.weaver/about.html">WebWeaver</A>: shareware page editor
<LI><A HREF="http://ogopogo.nttc.edu/tools/htmledit/HTMLedit.html">HTML.edit</A>: freeware which we recommend if constructing a set of many files
</UL>
There are several summary pages on the Web of HTML editors
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Computers/World_Wide_Web/HTML_Editors/Macintosh">yahoo</A>
</UL>
<HR>
<H2>HTML Goodies</H2>
This software is helpful for those working on more intense HTML projects
<UL>
<LI>Transparency: converts a chosen gif color to transparent
<LI><A HREF="http://www.city.net/cnx/software/webmap.html">WebMap</A>: for creating imagemap files
<LI>MSWord-->HTML converter: shareware
<LI>HTML Markup: drag and drop conversion of text to HTML
<LI>RTFtoHTML: converts RTF to HTML
</UL>
<HR>
