<DL>
<P>

<B>How do I hook up to the Web?</B>
<P>
Briefly, the information is organized for general viewers, and then for the UM
users.
Requirements:
<UL>
<LI>Hardware:This includes the computer microprocessor, the modem, and hard drive.
<LI>Software: Two kinds of software are identified.
<dd>Operating systems;  McIntosh, MS-DOS and Unix.
<dd>Connection system: Two commonly used are the University systems or
 commercial providers.</A>
 </UL>
<P>
For UM users:
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.itd.umich.edu/start//">ITD</A> For Home based computers.

<LI><A HREF="http://www.med.umich.edu:80/mcit/help/web-publish.html">MCIT</A> For UMMC based users

<P>
<A HREF="/web/help/wwwbis3.htm"> Some Some Background Notes </A>



