<TITLE>AACAP Awards</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY bgcolor=#FFFFFF text=#000000 link="#CC0000" alink="#FF3300">
<A HREF="/web/aacap/">Home</A> | <A HREF="/web/aacap/">Up</A> | <A HREF="http://www.psych.med.umich.edu/web/tools/">Tools</A> | <A HREF="/web/help/">Help</A> |
 
<HR>
<CENTER><img  src="/web/aacap/meeting/aacap.gif" > </center><BR clear=all> <center><H1> Website Awards</H1> </CENTER>


 



<img align=left src="/web/images/award/texas.gif"><BR>
<A HREF="http://swinfo.tamu.edu/gme/psych/"><IMG vspace=14 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"> <BR>The residency training in psychiatry at the <font=3>Texas A&M University - Scott & White</font=3></A> includes  special learning ressources for their students.<p>
We are the first website selected as providing the best educational material about mental health and mental disorders.<BR clear=all>




<img  src="http://www.coil.com/~grohol/badge.gif" border=0 align=right> <IMG vspace=10 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"> John M. Grohol started his best list of Mental Health Website. We are one of the first twelve.

<p><center><img  src="/web/images/award/interworld.gif"></center><BR clear=all>
<B><A HREF="http://pubs.iworld.com/iw-online/">The Internet World</B></A>, the Magazine for Internet Users list our page in the <B>Best list of Linda J. Engelman</B>, in their january 96 issue  <p>
&quot; when I think about the word best, the first thing that comes to mind are the dozens of nonprofit organizations and community outreach services that have establish a presence on the internet this year, These altruistic folks set an example for what is really possible, given the right tools, and they bring a sense of benevolence to an otherwise self-indulgent cyberworld.&quot;<BR>
<B>facts for families</B>. An excellent collection of pamphlets from the American Academy of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry.<BR>
<IMG hspace=6 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"><font size=-1> This material originally appeared in <A HREF="http://pubs.iworld.com/iw-online/">Internet World Magazine</A>, 
vol 7, number 1, january 1996; pp.33. 
Copyright&copy; 1995 Mecklermedia Corporation, 20 Ketchum Street, 
Westport, CT 06880; (203) 341-2802; info@mecklermedia.com; 
<http://www.iworld.com>. All rights reserved. Reprinted with permission.</font size=-1> 




