<H1>What's New in the days of June!</H1></CENTER>


The <A HREF="http://www.psych.med.umich.edu/web/pstar/">PsychStar</A> team is transitioning the workings of this website to the AACAP office in Washington, DC.  The AACAP is improving it's networking and setting up its own email system.  We hope this will lead to faster updates and better service.  We are now in the process of moving the server from the University of Michigan, and apologize for any temporary problems.<P>
The new URL for the server is: <B><A HREF="http://www.aacap.org/">http://www.aacap.org/</A></B><BR>
The new email for problems will be: <B><A HREF="mailto:webmaster@aacap.org">webmaster@aacap.org</A></B><BR>
- <A HREF="http://www.psych.med.umich.edu/web/UMpsych/staff/mhuang/">Milton Huang</A> for the entire PsychStar team

<P>
We are continuing to get awards :
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.pointcom.com/">the Top 5% on the web</A> by Point company
<LI>McKinley Group's <A HREF="http://www.mckinley.com/3star/3star.html">Magellan 3-Star Award</A>
</UL>

<UL>
<LI>The legislative alert page is updated. Please forward any comments or suggestions you have to the Department of Government Affairs.
</UL>
