<H2><A NAME="aacap_1996_Meetings">AACAP 1996 Meetings</A></H2>
<ul>
  <li><b>March 20-22, 1996</b>, Mid-Year Institute:<BR> 
"Update on Child Psychopharmacologic and
Psychotherapeutic Treatments," San Diego, CA.  The Mid-Year Institute is a comprehensive
examination of a single issue, disorder or treatment.<p>

  <li><b>April 14-26, 1996</b><BR>
Cruise of the Greek Islands and Turkey, including Athens and Mainland
Greece.  A unique opportunity to combine a professional program with colleagues and a
comprehensive travel program.</p>

  <li><b>June 26-29, 1996</b>,<BR> 21st Annual Review in Child and Adolescent Psychiatry, New York. The Review Course is a preparation for the Board Exam, as well as it serves as an up-to-date
review of child psychiatry.</p>

  <li><b>September 15, 1996,</b><BR>
 The Postgraduate Psychotherapy Institute for Child and Adolescent
Psychiatrists begins at 21 Bloomingdale Road, White Plains, NY.  Classes will be held in 4 one
hour sessions every other weekend on Sundays.  For registration or more information please
contact : </p>

Paulina F. Kernberg, M.D., Director, Postgraduate Psychotherapy Institute for Child &amp;
Adolescent Psychiatry at (914) 997-5951 or fax (914) 997-5723.<p>



  <li><b>October 22-27, 1996</b>,<BR> 43rd Annual Meeting, Philadelphia, PA.  Presenting the latest research
and clinical practice in the field of child and adolescent psychiatry.</p>
</ul>
