<IMG vspace=2 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"> <BR>
<h3><center>43rd Annual Meeting</h3>

<h3>October 22-27, 1996</h3>
<H3>Marriot Philadelphia</H3>
<h3>Philadelphia, <IMG hspace=12 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif">PA</h3>
</center>
<p><IMG vspace=4 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"> <BR>
<HR>
<h1>Call For Papers-1996 Annual Meeting</h1><IMG vspace=2 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"> <BR>
<p>



<h4>General Instructions</h4>
All submissions (papers, posters, institutes, symposia, media presentations, workshops, plenaries,
etc.) at the Annual Meeting of the American Academy of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry are
reviewed by the Scientific Program Committee.  Each submission must include:
<UL>
<LI>a Review Abstract, 
<LI>a Proceedings Extract, and 
<LI>the Abstract Cover Sheet. 
</UL>
 
The Review Abstract will be the basis of review by the committee; the
Proceedings Abstract will be published in the book of <i><B>Scientific Proceedings</B>.</i> <p>

<p>

<h5>Complete Instructions</h5>
For your complete set of Instructions and Procedures please call the AACAP Meetings
Department at (202) 966-7300.  This packet of information includes:<p>


<ul>
  <li>Review Abstract and Proceedings Abstract details</li>
  <li>Submission Essentials</li>
  <li>Deadlines</li>
  <li>Registration Fees</li>
  <li>Audio-Visual Equipment - Policies</li>
  <li>Audio Taping Information</li>
  <li>Presentation Descriptions</li>
  <li>Abstract Cover Sheet</li>
  <li>Suggestions for Preparing the Review Abstract</li>
  <li>Proceedings Abstract Form and Sample Illustrating Style</li>
</ul>
<p><HR>
