<HEAD>
<TITLE>words from the President</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY bgcolor=#FFFFFF text=#000000 link="#CC0000" alink="#FF3300">

<center><H1>A Word from the President of the American Academy of Child & Adolescent Psychiatry</H1></center>
<IMG vspace=6 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"> <BR>

<img align=left SRC= "/web/aacap/larrystone.gif">I am Larry Stone, a Child and Adolescent Psychiatrist practicing in San Antonio, Texas.  I am currently the President of the American Academy of Child & Adolescent Psychiatry. <P>

For many years, the Academy has been trying to help its members increase their knowledge and skill in the treatment of mental illness of children and their families throughout the United States and now throughout the world.  We have always been working hard to increase the level of knowledge and the level of expertise to prevent mental illness in children wherever they live. <P>

Currently, we are starting a violence initiative which we hope will be able to spread more information and skills in helping us prevent violence wherever it may occur.  The Academy will continue to work to inform its membership and to help them work with the others wherever they may be in the dealing within these issues.<P>

<center><B>Larry Stone, M.D.</B><p>
President of the American Academy of Child & Adolescent Psychiatry
<IMG vspace=6 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"> <BR>
 </center><P>
<HR>
