<HEAD>
<TITLE>PSI history</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#EEFFFF">
<IMG ALIGN="left" SRC="psilogo.gif" vspace=10 hspace=10><H1>Psychiatric Society for Informatics</H1>
<BR clear=all>
<P>
The PSI was started in 1995 at the Computers Applications in Mental Health meeting, run by Dr. Marvin Miller.  He chaired the first steering committee, which has subsequently established bylaws and incorporated as a non-profit organization, dedicated to promoting the understanding and use of    
informatics and information technology in Psychiatry. 
<HR>
Return <A HREF="/web/psi/">PSI homepage </A>
