<HEAD>
<TITLE>PSI newsletter</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#EEFFFF">

<IMG ALIGN="left" SRC="/web/psi/psilogo.gif" vspace=10 hspace=10><IMG vspace=8 SRC="/web/images/dot_clear.gif"><H1>Psychiatric Society <br>for Informatics</H1>
<BR clear=all>

<P><center>

<H2> Newsletter of the Psychiatric Society for Informatics</H2>

             <B> Volume 1, Issue 1  May 16, 1996</B> </center>

<P>


<B>The inaugural issue of the PSI Newsletter</B> 
<P>
This will be a periodic way of communicating to our membership. It is
being transmitted via our new listserv operated out of Indiana
University School of Medicine. 
<P>This issue will be brief as itis meant to test out the PSI Listserv. This issue will also be
mailed out to all the PSI members.
<P>
<B>First Annual PSI Meeting:</B>
<P>
On May 4, 1996 we met as a group of about 45 PSI members to
launch the Society. We met in the New York Hilton in
conjunction with the American Psychiatric Association annual
meeting. 
<P>Dr. John Greden gave the keynote address and helped us
trace the recent changes in psychiatry -- especially those that
relate to the need for computerization.
 Additional news</A> about
the meeting will be forthcoming in several publications.
<P>
A general membership meeting was held in the afternoon and was
followed by a meeting of the new Steering Committee.
<P> The
results of the election were announced and the Bylaws were
adopted. 
<P>The officers are:
<UL>
<LI> President, Marvin Miller, MD
<LI>President Elect, Norman Alessi, MD
<LI> Secretary/ Treasurer,Milton Huang, MD. 
<LI>The Steering Committee Members are: 
<DD>John Greist, MD
<DD>Sol Herman,MD
<DD>Joshua Freedman, MD
<DD>Seth Powsner,MD
<DD>Arlette Lefebvre, MD
<DD>Jesse Wright, MD.
</UL>
<P>
<B>Physicians Online:</B>
<P>
This service continues to expand in improve its online
offerings.  POL plans to offer full Internet access to all of
its users "within the next several months." They do plan to
incorporate the Netscape browser in their software.  This
should increase their current subscription (over 100,000
physicians) even more. POL does offer free E-mail now so this
may be of benefit to the PSI members who do not yet have E-mail.
POL will mail a copy of their newest software to all of
the PSI members in the near future.
<P>
<B>Position Papers:</B>
<P>
Several Steering Committee members have volunteered to work on
various position papers.  Hopefully they will send these
through the listserv and allow comments before they bring these
back to the Steering Committee for action.  Dr. Alessi will
draft a paper about violence and pornography on the internet.
Drs Freedman and Lefebvre will draft one about the positive
aspects of using the internet for mental health. Dr. Miller
will draft one about standard setting for computer programs
used in managed care.
<P>
<B>PSI Annual Meeting for 1996:</B>
<P>
The next annual meeting for us will be May 17, 1997 in San
Diego. Dr. Alessi will be the program chair and will form a
committee to assist him with this planning.

<B>Electronic Journal for PSI:</B>
<P>
Dr. Milton Huang will head a committee to start planning for an
electronic journal for our society. This will be a more formal
journal and should not be confused with this Newsletter.
<P>
<B>PSI Page on the Internet:</B>
<P>
Thanks to Milton Huang, MD, for the creation and the continued
work on this excellent Web page.
<P>
The URL is:   http://www.psych.med.umich.edu/web/psi
<P>
Our goals, membership application blanks, annual meeting
information, bylaws, etc can be found there. The heavy traffic
on Milton's page helps us get valuable exposure. Many thanks to
Milton for his outstanding work.








<HR>
