<H1><IMG SRC="milton.gif" WIDTH=117 HEIGHT=157 ALIGN=left>Welcome to
Milton's Homepage!</H1>

<P><BR clear=all>

I am currently a Lecturer in the University of Michigan Department of
Psychiatry and assistant director of the 


<a href="http://141.214.71.205/informat/index.htm">
UM Psychiatric Informatics
Program</A>. I am also the first graduate of the program, which is
directed by <A HREF="/web/UMpsych/staff/nalessi/">Dr. Norman
Alessi</A>.</P>

<P><B>Our current projects</B> include:</P>

<UL>
   <LI>providing Web serving services for the
   <A HREF="/web/UMpsych/">UM Department of Psychiatry</A> and the
   <A HREF="/web/aacap/">AACAP</A>. Their funding has allowed us to
   create our own server running off two power macs:
   <A HREF="/">Psychiatry Star</A>.
   
   <LI>creating a new national organization: the
   <A HREF="/web/psi/">Psychiatric Society for Informatics</A> (PSI)
   
   <LI>setting up a <A HREF="/web/UMpsych/infmatic/lecture/">Seminar
   series in medical informatics</A> for the University of Michgan
   Hospitals
   
   <LI>creating a Virtual Reality environment for acrophobia exposure
   in conjunction with the UM course,
   <A HREF="http://www.ummu.umich.edu/eng477/">Principles of Virtual
   Reality</A>, where I am a faculty advisor.
   
   <LI>setting up lectures for Psychiatry residents in medical
   informatics
   
   <LI>filming psychiatry patients to create a clinical video
   database
   
   <LI>creating interactive multimedia programs on CD-ROM
   
   <LI>setting up telemedicine links for the University of Michgan
   Hospital for remote examination
</UL>

<P><B>Some recent papers</B>:<BR>

</P>

<UL>


   <LI>Huang M P and Alessi N E.
   <A HREF="http://www.appi.org/ajp/july96/ajp7toc.html#AJPjuly96-17">The
   Future of Psychiatry and the Internet</A>. American Journal of
   Psychiatry. (July 1996); 153: 861-869. 
<A HREF="/web/UMpsych/staff/mhuang/papers/AJPinternet.htm">FullText</A>
 is available, courtesy of the American Journal.
<P>

   
   <LI>Alessi N E and Huang M P.
   <A HREF="/web/psytimes/3wave.htm">Riding the Third Wave:
   Psychiatry in the Information Era</A>. Psychiatric Times. (June
   1996); 13 (6): 20.
   
   <LI>Huang M P and Alessi N E.
   <A HREF="http://www.psych.med.umich.edu/web/psytimes/psychwww.htm">Psychiatry
   Navigates the Web</A>. Psychiatric Times. (1995 Aug) 32-33.
   
   <LI>Alessi N and Huang M
   <A HREF="http://www.psych.med.umich.edu/web/psytimes/infofelw.htm">U
   of Michigan On-Line with 1st Psychiatric Informatics
   Fellowship</A>. Psychiatric Times. (1995 Aug) 34-35.
</UL>

<P><B>I plan to be presenting</B> at the following meetings:</P>

<UL>
   <LI>I will be at the American Association of Directors of Psychiatric Residency Training (AADPRT) meeting from January 16-21, 1997, in South Carolina.  I will present on the elements of an Informatics curriculum in Psychiatric Residency training. on the 17th at 12:30pm.
   
   <LI>I am a program co-chair for the <A HREF="/web/psi/mtg/">PSI
   annual meeting</A> scheduled for May 17th, 1997 in San Diego.
</UL>

<P><B>&nbsp;</B></P>


<B>Research interests</B><P>

<UL>
   <LI>use of multimedia to capture mental status information
   
   <LI>computer models of cognition
   
   <LI>the impact of information technology on perceptions of self
   and relationships
   
   <LI>organizational factors affecting the implementation of
   information technology
</UL>

<P>Of course, most of my time is divided between clinical duties, informatics projects, writing papers and giving lectures and workshops.</P>



<P>If you want to contact me, e-mail me at
<A HREF="mailto:mhuang@umich.edu">mhuang@umich.edu</A> or write.</P>

<P>My official address is:</P>

<DL>
   <DD>Dr. Milton Huang<BR>
   
   University of Michigan, Department of Psychiatry<BR>
   
   1500 E. Medical Center Drive, Box 0390<BR>
   
   Ann Arbor, MI 48109-0390<BR>
   
   telephone: (313) 763-2015<BR>
   
   fax: (313) 936-8907<BR>
</DL>   
