<IMG SRC="/web/images/pstaricn.gif" align="left"><H1>Information Sources</H1><BR CLEAR = ALL>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="webinfo">Web-based information sources</A></H3>
<UL>



<LI><A HREF="http://www.mentalhealth.com/">Internet Mental Health</A>: an extensive free encyclopedia of mental health information.
<LI><A HREF="/web/aacap/factsFam/">Facts for Families</A>
<li>the <A HREF="http://www.informatik.fh-luebeck.de/icd/welcome.html">ICD-10 Chapter V (F)</A> is available from the FRG as part of a joint project to be carried out by the Medical University of Lbeck Department of Psychiatry as a WHO Collaborating Center for Training and Research in Mental Health 
<LI><A HREF="http://www.princeton.edu/~harnad/psyc.html">Psycoloquy</A>: a refereed journal on "all areas of psychology as well as cognitive science, neuroscience, behavioral biology, artificial intelligence, robotics/vision, linguistics and philosophy"
<LI><A HREF="http://www.cityscape.co.uk/users/ad88/psych.htm">Psychiatry On-Line</A>: edited by <A HREF="http://www.cityscape.co.uk/users/ad88/bgreen.htm">Dr. Ben Green</A>, MB, ChB, MRCPsych
<LI><A HREF="http://www.well.com:80/user/selfhelp/">Self-Help Psychology Magazine</A>: edited by Marlene Maheu, Ph.D.
<LI><A HREF="http://www.med.harvard.edu/publications/Mental/.index.html">Harvard Mental Health Letter</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.mhsource.com">Mental Health InfoSource </A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.ama-assn.org/journals/standing/psyc/psychome.htm">Archives of General Psychiatry</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.appi.org/ajp.htm">American Journal of Psychiatry</A>


</UL>

<HR>
<H3><A NAME="summaries">web-based directories to more information:</A></H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.interport.net/~mpulier/psyjumps.html">Myron Pulier's list of Psychiatric Resources</A>
<LI><A HREF="
http://freenet.msp.mn.us/ip/health/stockley/mental_health.html">Herb Stockley's Internet Mental Health Resources</A>
<LI>The Mental Health page from <A HREF="http://www.cc.emory.edu/WHSCL/medweb.mentalhealth.html" NAME="">Emory's MedWeb</A>
<LI>The Psychiatry page from the <A HREF="http://galaxy.einet.net/galaxy/Medicine/Medical-Specialties/Psychiatry.html" NAME="">EINet Galaxy</A>
<LI>The Psychiatry page from <A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Health/Medicine/Psychiatry/" NAME="">Yahoo</A>
<LI>Paul Fehrmann's list of <A HREF="http://www.n2h2.com/KOVACS/S0055s.html ">Psychology and Psychiatry electronic conferences</A>
<LI>the <A HREF="http://http2.sils.umich.edu/Public/nirg/nirg1.html">Neurosciences Internet Resouce Guide</A> from the University of Michigan School of Information and Library Studies.  This list contains pointers to locations of interest in the Neurosciences.
</UL>

<HR>
<H3><A NAME="software">Sites for software:</A></H3>
<UL>
<LI>Anonymous ftp site at <A HREF="ftp://ftp.iupui.edu/pub">Indiana University School of Medicine</A> maintained by Dr. Marvin Miller.
<LI><A HREF="ftp://ftp.stolaf.edu/pub/macpsych/">MacPsych</A>: an anonymous FTP site at St. Olaf college aimed at psychologists who use Macintosh computers
</UL>

<HR>
<H3><A NAME="newsgroups">Newsgroups:</A></H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="news: sci.med.psychobiology">sci.med.psychobiology</A>: discusses topics in psychiatry and psychobiology
<LI><A HREF="news: sci.psychology.digest">sci.psychology.digest</A>: discusses general issues in psychology and contains articles from PSYCOLOQUY
<LI>bionet.neuroscience.amyloid: the <A HREF="news:bionet.neuroscience.amyloid">Alzheimer's research newsgroup</A>
</UL>
If you are interested in finding about other mental health newsgroups, check out John Grohol's <A HREF="http://chat.carleton.ca/~tscholbe/psych.html" NAME="">Psychology & Support Groups Newsgroup Pointer</A>

