<TITLE>Medical Student Electives</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="EEEEEE">
<B> <IMG hspace=3 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"><A HREF="/">Home</A> | <A HREF="./">Up</A> | <A HREF="/web/tools/">Tools</A> | <A HREF="/web/help/">Help</A> | <A HREF="/web/scripts/comment.acgi">Send a comment</A></B>
<HR>
<H1>Medical student electives</H1>
<P>

	A variety of fourth-year electives are available for medical students in the Department of Psychiatry at the University of Michigan.  Clinical as well as research opportunities can be arranged.  Students from other medical schools are welcome, and those interested in learning more about Michigan's Psychiatry Residency program are invited to spend some elective time here.  <P>

For more information, contact: <P>

	Kenneth Chamberlain, M.D.<BR>

	(313) 769-7100, extension 5487<P>

or<P>

	Rachel Glick, M.D<BR>

	(313) 936-5900 <P>
<HR>
Continue on to learn about the <A HREF="resident.htm">residency program</A>.
