<HEAD>
<TITLE>Residency Program</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="EEEEEE">
<B> <IMG hspace=3 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"><A HREF="/">Home</A> | <A HREF="./">Up</A> | <A HREF="/web/tools/">Tools</A> | <A HREF="/web/help/">Help</A> | <A HREF="/web/scripts/comment.acgi">Send a comment</A></B>
<HR>
<H1>Residency</H1>

	Every resident is an individual with unique goals and specific needs. Our residency program tries to customize each resident's experience to meet those needs. Every resident also must master the basics in specified areas of psychiatry. Thus, we offer a detailed didactic <A HREF="#curriculum">core curriculum</A> and a series of rotations to promote this mastery. <P>

	The setting is academic but not ivory tower. Psychiatry residents at the University of Michigan are responsible for the care of a wide variety of patients who present the full range of psychiatric disorders.  Though case loads are generally small, the clinical work is demanding and requires substantial effort and time.  Supervision is similarly intensive; on most rotations, an hour of supervision is provided for each three to four hours of patient contact. <P>

<HR>
<H2><A NAME="index">RESIDENT ROTATIONS</A></H2>
<A HREF="#PGY1">PGY-I</A>

<PRE>
(4 mos)			         		              (4 mos)					                (2 mos)
