<TITLE>Geropsychiatry</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="EEEEEE">
<B> <IMG hspace=3 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"><A HREF="/">Home</A> | <A HREF="./">Up</A> | <A HREF="/web/tools/">Tools</A> | <A HREF="/web/help/">Help</A> | <A HREF="/web/scripts/comment.acgi">Send a comment</A></B>
For general comments or suggestions about the Department of Psychiatry Website please contact Randolph Nesse, M.D. at <A HREF="mailto:nesse@umich.edu">nesse@umich.edu</A><BR>
<H1>Geropsychiatry Division</H1><P>
Director - Alan Mellow, M.D., Ph.D.<P>
		The aging of the population has created a growing need for training experiences in geriatric psychiatry.  The University of Michigan Geropsychiatry Division, founded five years ago and led by Alan M. Mellow, M.D., Ph.D., provides clinical psychiatric care for elderly patients, with specialized expertise in dementia, geriatric depression, late-life psychoses and other mental disorders of old age.  The program offers training experiences for medical students and residents through clinical rotations, didactic sessions and an ongoing journal club.  There is also a <A HREF="../gerifelw.htm">post-residency fellowship</A> program for trained psychiatrists who wish to obtain subspecialty training and certification in Geriatric Psychiatry, as well as research training in the field.  The Division has recently  received federal funding for a training grant for a geriatric fellowship program that links geriatric medicine, geriatric dentistry and the departments of Family Practice, Neurology and Psychiatry.<P>

		Clinical rotations in geropsychiatry include a specialized geriatric psychiatry inpatient team at the <A HREF="vamc.htm">Veterans Administration Hospital</A>, as well as outpatient consultation clinics at both the VAMC and University Hospitals.  <P>

		Research is an integral part of the Geropsychiatry Division, where studies are under way involving new drug therapies for Alzheimer's disease and other dementias as well as on the biology and treatment of geriatric alcoholism.
For general comments or suggestions about the Department of Psychiatry Website please contact Randolph Nesse, M.D. at <A HREF="mailto:nesse@umich.edu">nesse@umich.edu</A><BR>
