<H1>Managed Care Division</H1><P>
Director - Kevin Kerber, M.D.<P>
	If there is such a thing as "primary care psychiatry," it's happening in the Managed Care Division, says Kevin Kerber, M.D., Director of the Managed Care Division.<P>

	"We handle everyday mental health difficulties," he explains. "A lot of these people have not been treated before, so we make a lot of new diagnoses. There's also a lot of collaborative work with our patients' primary care physicians."<P>

	The program handles approximately 5,000 visits each year through the University of Michigan's HMO, M-CARE.  Psychiatrists and social workers handle a broad range of issues, such as depression, anxiety and difficulties with marriage, family and children, he says. They provide phone intake, evaluation and short-term counseling or medication treatment. Patients may also be referred to Department of Psychiatry faculty or community agencies for further assistance. <P>

	The program is already primed for health care reform: a key goal is managing care in a cost-effective manner. Utilization reviews of all outpatient referrals and inpatient stays are an essential part of their practice. <P>
<HR>
