<TITLE>Clinical Operations</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="EEEEEE">
<B> <IMG hspace=3 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"><A HREF="/">Home</A> | <A HREF="./">Up</A> | <A HREF="/web/tools/">Tools</A> | <A HREF="/web/help/">Help</A> | <A HREF="/web/scripts/comment.acgi">Send a comment</A></B>
<HR>
<H1>Coordination of Clinical Operations</H1> - Kenneth Silk, M.D.<P>

	Although residents do almost all of their work at University Hospital or at the Veteran's Hospital across the river, the Department's clinical operations are far-flung, with sites in neighboring communities and at several other sites in Ann Arbor. Coordination of all these clinical operations is the job of Kenneth Silk, M.D., Associate Chair for Clinical and Academic Affairs.  <P>

	Dr. Silk combines his Yale training with extensive experience at the Ann Arbor VAMC, in private practice, and, most recently, running the Adult Service, the Personality Disorders Program and the 9C inpatient unit.  He is scrambling to find ways for the Department to take advantage of opportunities to make our system more accessible for patients, a task that these days means tough negotiations with managed care providers, in addition to attention to our own operations.  He is also coordinating plans for the psychiatry portion of the new East Medical Campus, now under construction, which will become the main site for outpatient operations.  <P>

	He is creating a system in which computers and effective administrative structures make every member of the Department part of a single efficient organism that can respond quickly to a rapidly changing environment.
<HR>
