<H1>Benefits</H1>

<H2>Dental Insurance:</H2>
	Available after one year of employment.<P>

<H2>Health Insurance:</H2>
	Basic Blue Cross/Blue Shield premiums are paid by the 
	University.<P>

<H2>Life Insurance:</H2>
	Low-cost group coverage is available.<P>

<H2>Malpractice Insurance:</H2>
	Provided by the University at no charge for patients seen in the training program.<P>

<H2>Maternity Leave:</H2>

	One month with pay, extended leave without pay.  No overnight call during last trimester and first two months after delivery.<P>

<H2>Paternity Leave:</H2>

	Being discussed and negotiated.<P>

<H2>Stipend Levels:</H2>

	Negotiated annually by the House Officers' Association.  House

	Officers must either pay association dues or a representation

	service fee as a condition of employment.<P>

<H2>Vacation:</H2>

	PGY I's have three weeks. All other House Officers

	have four weeks annually.<P>

