<H1>Application information</H1>

	Materials needed to complete an application are:
	
<UL>
<LI>	Application form
<LI>	Brief personal statement 
<LI>	Medical school transcript
<LI>	Dean's letter from medical school
<LI>	Letters of recommendation from three people who personally know the applicant's work.
</UL>
<P>
	A day of interviews is required.  Most are arranged in the fall and winter of the year before training is to begin.  Four weeks notice about proposed visits will make it possible to schedule interviews with faculty members who are working in areas of special interest to the applicant.  The application should be completed and received before a visit is scheduled.<P>

	The Resident Selection Committee meets regularly from October to February to consider applications.  Except in unusual circumstances, all first year positions are arranged through the NRMP.<P>

	The University of Michigan, as an equal opportunity/affirmative action employer, complies with all applicable federal and state laws regarding non-discrimination and affirmative action, including Title IX of the Education Amendments of 1972 and Section 504 of the Rehabilitation Act of 1973. The University of Michigan is committed to a policy of non-discrimination and equal opportunity for all persons regardless of race, sex, color, religion, creed, national origin or ancestry, age, marital status, sexual orientation, disability, or Vietnam-era veteran status in employment, educational programs and activities, and admissions. Inquiries or complaints may be addressed to the University's Director of Affirmative Action and Title IX/Section 504 Coordinator, 4005 Wolverine Tower, Ann Arbor, Michigan 48109-1281, (313) 763-0235, TDD (313) 747-1388, Fax (313) 763-2891. University of Michigan Information: (313) 764-1817.<P>


For application materials or further information please contact:<P>
Michelle Riba, M.D.<BR>
Director of Resident and Fellow Education<BR>
Department of Psychiatry<BR>
University of Michigan<BR>
CFOB Building, Room B2902<BR>
1500 E. Medical Center Dr.<BR>
Ann Arbor, MI  48109-0704<BR>
(313) 764-6875<BR>
<A HREF="mailto:mriba@umich.edu">mriba@umich.edu</A>
