<UL><LI><B>Attendance</B>:  Each psychiatry resident, in order to receive credit for    
                   rotation is expected to attend each seminar attendance 
                   expectations are best met during their C/L rotations,
                   <U><U>the entire series is being given three times per year 
                   (every four months).  Medical students doing C/L
                   psychiatry are asked to attend.</UL><P>

<UL><LI><B>Co-ordinator:</B>        Mary Lou Veasman (phone 763 1573) (working with David 
                   Knesper)</UL><P>

<UL><LI><B>Reading Material: </B>   Before each seminar, the residents and faculty leader
             
                          will be asked to read the relevant chapter from Alan 
                          Stoudemire and Barry Fogel's edited book,"Psychiatric
                          care of the Medical Patient".  The faculty leader may 
                          provide additional reading materials.  Mary Lou will 
                          distribute reading materials and retaian copies
                          for the syllabus being developed.  Please contact 
                          Mary Lou to request the reading in the event you 
                          do a non-C/L rotation.</UL>
