<B> <IMG hspace=3 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"><A HREF="/">Home</A> | <A HREF="/">Up</A> | <A HREF="/web/tools/">Tools</A> | <A HREF="/web/help/">Help</A> | <A HREF="/web/scripts/comment.acgi">Send a comment</A></B><HR>

<B>New Mental Health Code</B>
<P>
Notification by Dr. Cameron and Dr. Carli
<P>
This very important issue came up today during the Dept. of Mental Health licensing survey.  We were told that this new law actually goes into effect tomorrow.  
<P>
While some of the specific interpretations of the law await legislative "rules", we know this:  All patients who are prescribed a psychotropic must be given information about the drug.  This goes for inpatient & outpatient.  
<P>
It applies to physicians and nurses.  Currently, it is being interpreted as requiring WRITTEN information.  
<P>
And this does not substitute for the patient signing an "informed consent" form.  <P>We're clearly not ready for this change.  We have however (thru Ollie & Ila Atwood & Karen Milner) developed 28 different drug handouts that will be used at Riverview.
<P>  
If you wish a copy of these handouts, let Ila or me know and we'll sent via enclosure.  
<P>
These patient handouts come from our Pharmacy & you can access the same info via INS, on line reference information system, #3microMedex Clinical Information, Aftercare, Drug leaflets. 
<P> The forms Ila did, took the Pharmacy info, formated in Word with patient information included, + Karen Milner edited some of them.  For right now, please continue to also use the informed consent form.  
<P>
We will need to modify this as we get further rulings about what is required under new law(s).  Thanks.

--
<HR>
