<TITLE>Joining the AACAP</TITLE>
<!-- This document was created from RTF source by rtftohtml version
2.7.3 -->
</head><BODY bgcolor=#FFFFFF text=#000000 link="#CC0000" alink="#FF3300">
<A HREF="/web/aacap/">Home</A> | <A HREF="./">Up</A> | <A HREF="http://www.psych.med.umich.edu/web/tools/">Tools</A> | <A HREF="/web/help/">Help</A> | http://www.psych.med.umich.edu/web/aacap/
<HR>

<h1>AACAP Membership</h1><p>
<p>
<b>An Invitation</b><p>
<p>
The American Academy of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry invites you to join the
ranks of 5,800 members in their efforts to address the needs of children,
adolescents and their families.  Membership is open to:<p>

 child and adolescent psychiatrists,<br>
 general psychiatrists with primary interest in child and adolescent
psychiatry,<br>
 physicians with strong ties to the field of child and adolescent psychiatry,<br>
 residents of child and adolescent or general psychiatry training programs,
and<br>
 medical students.<br>
<p>
<b>AACAP Member Benefits</b><p>
<p>
AACAP members enjoy subscriptions to the monthly <i>Journal of the American
Academy of Child &amp; Adolescent Psychiatry</i>, bi-monthly <i>AACAP News</i>,
and newsletters on Managed Care and Research.  Residents and Medical Students
receive their own newsletter, <i>Developmentor</i>.  The Academy also provides
various publications on prevention, peer review, and insurance, as well as an
extensive public information network.  Other benefits include a Liability
Insurance Program designed specifically for child and adolescent psychiatrists,
and various consumer discount programs.<p>
<p>
<b>Membership Categories</b><p>
<p>
<b>Active Member</b> - Physicians who have completed two years of child and
adolescent psychiatry training and two years of general psychiatry training.
Annual dues $275.<p>
<p>
<b>Fellow Member</b> - Physicians who are board certified in child and
adolescent psychiatry by the American Board of Psychiatry and Neurology in
Child and Adolescent Psychiatry, have been in practice for at least five years,
and have a major professional interest and activity in the field of child and
adolescent psychiatry.  Annual dues $275.<p>
<p>
<b>Affiliate Member</b> - Physicians who are not trained in child and
adolescent psychiatry, but are making contributions to the field of child and
adolescent psychiatry.  Annual dues $225.<p>
<p>
<b>Corresponding Member</b> - Physicians who are eligible for the preceding
categories of membership who live outside of the United States or Canada.
Annual dues $150.<p>
<p>
<b>Child and Adolescent Psychiatry Resident Member</b> - Physicians who are
currently enrolled in a child and adolescent psychiatry training program.
Annual dues $50.<p>
<p>
<p>
<b>General Psychiatry Resident Member</b> - Physicians who are currently
enrolled in a general psychiatry training program.  Annual dues $50.<p>
<p>
<b>Medical Student Member</b> - Students who are enrolled in medical school.
Annual dues $25.<p>
<hr>
<h2>More Information</h2><p>
<p>
For more information about AACAP membership or to obtain an application, please
call, write or fax to:<p>
<p>
AACAP Membership Department<br>
3615 Wisconsin Avenue, N.W.<br>
Washington, DC  20016-3007<br>
U.S. Toll-free: 1-800-333-7636<br>
Tel. (202) 966-7300<br>
Fax (202) 966-2891<br>
E-mail:  <a href="mailto:membership@aacap.org">membership@aacap.org</a><br>
<p>
When requesting an application, please indicate the category of membership you
are applying for.  Also, please acknowledge receiving this information from the
AACAP Website.  Thank you.<p>
<p>
<b>Prepared:</b> June 1995.<p>
<HR><A HREF="/web/aacap/">Home</A> | <A HREF="./">Up</A> | <A HREF="http://www.psych.med.umich.edu/web/tools/">Tools</A> | <A HREF="/web/help/">Help</A> | <A HREF="/web/scripts/aacapcomment.acgi">send a comment</A>| http://www.psych.med.umich.edu/web/aacap/<!--FOOT-->
