<head>

<TITLE>Dept of Gov Affairs: Action Request</TITLE>
</head>
<BODY bgcolor=#FFFFFF text=#000000 link="#CC0000" alink="#FF3300">
| <A HREF="/web/aacap/">Home</A> | <A HREF="/web/aacap/govafair/">Up</A> | <A HREF="http://www.psych.med.umich.edu/web/tools/">Tools</A> | <A HREF="/web/help/">Help</A> |http://www.psych.med.umich.edu/web/aacap/

<HR><IMG SRC= "/web/aacap/logogov.gif"width=200 height=110 align=left border=1> <BR>

 <center><h2>How to contact the legislators <BR>&<BR> Let us know about your action</h2></center>


<A HREF="/web/aacap/">Home</A> | <A HREF="/web/aacap/govafair/legalert.htm">Current Alert</A> |<A HREF="/web/aacap/govafair/terms.htm"> Glossary</A> | <A HREF="/web/aacap/govafair/contact.htm">Contact Legislators </A>| <A HREF="/web/aacap/govafair/archive.htm">Archives</A>| legal issues |  <A HREF="/web/aacap/govafair/fax.htm">send back</A> | <A HREF="/web/aacap/govafair/index.htm">Index</A> | <A HREF="/web/aacap/govafair/survey.htm"> Survey </A><BR clear=all><HR noshade>

<IMG vspace=2 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"> <BR>
<B><font size=6>T</font size=6></B>hank you for accessing the AACAP goverment affairs' page. <p>

The AACAP's Department of Government Affairs has prepared several items which should make the contacts with your Congressional representatives as easy and quick as possible.  The following items are available to assist you:
<ul>
<li><b><A HREF="legalert.htm">Legislative Alert</A></b>, provides background information and "message" sound bites on pending legislation .
<LI><b>Sample letters</b> can be tailored to your liking for faxing/mailing and e-mailing to Congressional offices. The sample letters can be downloaded from the AACAP's home page, modified, and mailed, faxed or e-mailed directly to your Representative and Senators national offices.<br>

<li><b><A HREF="fax.htm">Fax-Back Evaluation Form</A></b>, this form should be sent back to the AACAP's Department of Government Affairs in order to let us know about your actions. Please, use Fax or E-mail as often as possible. <br>

<LI><B><A HREF="terms.htm"> Glossary of Legislative Terms</A></B>reprinted from the AMA Guide to Communicating with Members of Congress,

</ul>
<p>
<HR>
<h2>How to contact the legislators</h2>

<font size=4>Whether you are calling or writing Washington or the field office or visiting them, 
let them know you are a Child and Adolescent Psychiatrist and a constituent. </font size=4>
<p>

<h3>Calling, Writing, Faxing</h3>

All members of Congress can be reached by calling the U.S. Capitol operator at:<br>
<B>(202) 224-3121</B>.  The operator will connect you to the requested office.<P>

Phone numbers for state and district offices can be found in your local phone book.<P>

The office staff can give you the address and fax numbers for state and
district offices. <P>

Letters to the Washington offices can be addressed as
follows: 
<UL>
<LI>House of Representatives:  The Honorable..., U.S. House of Representatives, Washington, D.C.  20515 
<LI>Senate: The Honorable...., U.S.Senate, Washington, D.C. 20510.
</UL>
<p>



<h3>E-mailing</h3><p>
The Department of Government Affairs has expanded its use of electronic
communication.  We have provided you with the World Wide Web location that lists all of the available e-mail addresses for members of Congress:
<UL>
<LI>  <a href="http://www.lib.umich.edu/libhome/Documents.center/federal.html">the U of M library</a> WWW interface :
&lt;http://www.lib.umich.edu/libhome/Documents.center/federal.html&gt;.</UL><P>
<UL>
<LI>the <a href="gopher://una.hh.lib.umich.edu:70/11/socsci/poliscilaw/uslegi">ULIBRARY</a> Gopher's web interface:
&lt;gopher://una.hh.lib.umich.edu:70/11/socsci/poliscilaw/uslegi &gt; 
</UL><p>


<H3><B>Visiting</B></H3>

 Your Congressional representatives are in their state and district offices during the Congressional Recess in August and they need to hear from you on these issues.  This is a perfect time to contact them. In addition to the regular forms of contact, such as writing and calling your
Congressional representatives, the recess period (august) offers you an opportunity to visit the state and district offices, attend a townmeeting, arrange a breakfast or lunch meeting, join with a consumer group (NAMI, NMHA, Federations of Families) representative to set up a visit.<p>

<HR>
<H2>Let us know about your activities</H2> 

Mary Crosby, Deputy Executive Director 
Tracey Crowell, Deputy Director of Government Affairs 
Jennifer Dexter, Research & Government Affairs Assistant 

If you have any questions, please :
<UL>
<LI>call  (800) 333-7636.
<LI>e-mail  gov@aacap.org
<LI>fax 1-202 966 2891
</UL>
Don't forget to use the &quot;Fax Back/  Send-Back form&quot;.
      

<p>
<b>Thank you in advance for taking the time to contact your legislators and for
letting us know about your activities.</b><p></font size=4>

