      </TD></TR>
   <TR>
      <TD>
         <P>Telnet
      </TD><TD>
         <P>This protocol uses a client/server model where users
         (clients) connect to a serving computer like a local
         terminal. This enables users at a distance to perform all
         the same functions a local terminal user can perform.
      </TD><TD>
         <P>Food and Drug Administration:
         &lt;telnet://fdabbs.fda.gov&gt;</P>
         
         <P>Medline:</P>
         
         <P>&lt;telnet://um-medline.bih.harvard.edu
      </TD></TR>
   <TR>
      <TD>
         <P>Gopher
      </TD><TD>
         <P>This protocol uses a client/server model which organizes
         information on different computers in menus that can be
         linked together. Information requests are made by simply
         choosing an appropriate menu selection.
      </TD><TD>
         <P>NIH guide to grants and contracts:
         &lt;gopher://gopher.nih.gov:70/11/res/nih-guide&gt;</P>
         
