<HEAD><TITLE>Annual Meeting</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#EEFFFF">
<center><H2>PSI Annual Meeting</H2>
<H2>Psychiatric Informatics: it's role in the New Psychiatry</H2>
<B>Saturday May 4th, 1996, New York City</B></center><P><IMG vspace=6 SRC="/web/images/dot_clear.gif">
The first annual meeting of the Psychiatric Society for Informatics (PSI) will be held on Saturday May 4th, 1996 in New York City.  It's theme is "Psychiatric Informatics: it's role in the New Psychiatry."<P>  
The keynote speaker is <B>Dr. John Greden</B> who will be talking about the New Psychiatry and the dramatic changes affecting our field. Co-program chairs for this event are <B>
Dr. Norman Alessi</B> and <B>Dr. Milton Huang.</B>  Please direct comments and questions to them : <BR>
<IMG hspace=10 SRC="/web/images/dot_clear.gif">
<BR>1500 E. Medical Center Drive, Box 0390, Ann Arbor, MI 48109-0390, <BR>Email: mhuang@umich.edu<P>

REGISTRATION
<UL>

<LI>Preregistration is $100 for non-members and $75 for members.  Resident rate is $50 for non-members and $25 for members.  Deadline for preregistration is April 20th.  All charges go up by $25 for registration on-site.  Lunch will be provided.

<LI>Checks should be made out to the Psychiatric Society for Informatics and sent to 
<UL>
<LI><B> Marvin Miller, MD</B> 1315 W 10th St., Indianapolis IN 46202.
 E-mail:izau100@indyunix.iupui.edu
</UL>

<LI><A HREF="regform.htm">Registration forms</A> and updated information is available at our website: http://www.psych.med.umich.edu/web/psi/
</UL>
<P>
<B> Location is the Nassau Suite, 2nd floor, New York Hilton Hotel</B>
<P>
