<TITLE>Milton's InterPsych Page</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#EEFFFF">
<B><A HREF="/">Home</A> | <A HREF="/">Up</A> | <A HREF="/web/tools/">Tools</A> | <A HREF="/web/help/">Help</A> | <A HREF="/web/scripts/comment.acgi">Send a comment</A></B>
<HR>
<H1><A NAME="index">Milton's InterPsych page</A></H1>

<H2>InterPsych Index</H2>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="#intro">Introduction</A> to InterPsych
<LI><A HREF="#goals">Goals</A> of InterPsych
<LI><A HREF="#services">Services</A> provided by InterPsych
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="ipn.htm">The Interpsych Newsletter</A>
<LI><A HREF="forum.htm">InterPsych's Scholarly Electronic Conferences</A>
  <UL>
  <LI>with a <A HREF="forum.htm#slist">short list of available conferences</A> (including how to subscribe or unsubscribe)
  <LI>and a longer <A HREF="longlist.htm">expanded list</A> that describes each conference
  </UL>
<LI><A HREF="ircconf.htm">Real-time Conferences</A>
</UL>
<LI><A HREF="#board">Board Members</A>
</UL>
<HR>
<H2><A NAME="intro">Introduction</A></H2>
InterPsych is a non-profit making, voluntary organization, established on the Internet with the aim of promoting international scholarly collaboration on inter-disciplinary research and intervention efforts in the field of psychopathology.  The organization offers a variety of scholarly electronic conferences via e-mail, and real time conferences.  Plans are underway for an electronically distributed journal.
<P>
InterPsych has over 8000 members throughout the world, including many leading academics, research scientists, clinical practitioners, and students.  Our membership is drawn fromdisciplines as diverse as anthropology, computer science, neuroscience, pharmacology, philosophy, psychiatry, psychology,and sociology.
<P>
Return to <A HREF="#index">InterPsych Index</A><P>
<HR>
<H2><A NAME="goals">Goals</A></H2>
InterPsych has two main aims:
<OL>
<LI>To foster interdisciplinary debate and empirical collaborationon all aspects of psychopathology.  We believe that an eclectic approach will produce refinements in the theory and practice of psychiatry and clinical psychology.

<LI>To encourage and promote the use of the vast resources of the Internet by both academics and clinical practitioners.  The Internet offers the possibility of rapid dissemination of research findings, and ease in conducting discussions over disciplinary and geographic boundaries.
</OL>
Return to <A HREF="#index">InterPsych Index</A><P>
<HR>
<H2><A NAME="services">Services</A></H2>
To fulfill these aims INTERPSYCH has set up the following electronic 
resources for its members:
<P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="ipn.htm">The Interpsych Newsletter</A>
<LI><A HREF="forum.htm">InterPsych's Scholarly Electronic Conferences</A>
<LI><A HREF="ircconf.htm">Real-time Conferences</A>
</UL><P>
Return to <A HREF="#index">InterPsych Index</A><P>
<HR>
<H2><A NAME="board">InterPsych Board Members</A></H2>

The board compositions is currently under reorganization and will be updated someday
<P>
Return to <A HREF="#index">InterPsych Index</A>
