<HEAD>
<TITLE>Tony Aguirre</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="EEEEEE">

<B> <IMG hspace=3 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"><A HREF="/">Home</A> | <A HREF="./">Up</A> | <A HREF="/web/tools/">Tools</A> | <A HREF="/web/help/">Help</A> | <A HREF="/web/scripts/comment.acgi">Send a comment</A></B>
<HR>
<H2>TonyAguirre</H2>
<P>
I'm Tony Aguirre; In August 1993 I was appointed Director of the Taubman Medical Library and Coordinator of the Health Sciences Libraries on campus.
<P>
My previous position was as IAIMS librarian at Columbia  University, where I was responsible for integrating library and  clinical files, as well as developing management systems for  Medical Logic Modules, part of the clinical information system.
<P>
I was also a member of the UMLS contract (with the National  Library of Medicine) team where my interest was (and still is)  query analysis and representation.
<P>
Before that I was director of the Library of the College of  Physicians of Philadelphia.And,BL (before librarianship) I was a research biochemist.
<P>
My e-mail address is <A HREF="mailto:tonyra@t.imap.itd.umich.edu">tonyra@t.imap.itd.umich.edu</A>
