<TITLE>Electronic Medical Record
</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="EEEEEE">
<B> <IMG hspace=3 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"><A HREF="/">Home</A> | <A HREF="./">Up</A> | <A HREF="/web/tools/">Tools</A> | <A HREF="/web/help/">Help</A> | <A HREF="/web/scripts/comment.acgi">Send a comment</A></B>
<HR>
<H2>Electronic Medical Record and Medical Decision Support -- Applying Medical
Informatics
</H2>
by William F. Bria II, M.D.
<P> 


Clinical information systems today have become a critical component in
guiding clinical decision support and efforts to maintain and improve the
quality of care as the managed care process grows throughout the United
States.   Dr. Bria will review a model of clinical information systems that
best support physicians, nurses, and others in accommodating the change in
American healthcare, as well as provide examples of new systems designed to
bring the latest technology to bear on these difficult problems.


<HR>
Return to the <A HREF="./">Lecture Series</A> table



