<B> <IMG hspace=3 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"><A HREF="/">Home</A> | <A HREF="./">Up</A> | <A HREF="/web/tools/">Tools</A> | <A HREF="/web/help/">Help</A> | <A HREF="/web/scripts/comment.acgi">Send a comment</A></B>
<HR>

<H2>William F. Bria II</H2>


William F. Bria II, M.D., is the Medical Director of Clinical Information
Systems, the Medical Director of the Critical Care Medical Unit, and an
Assistant Professor of  Medicine in the Department of Internal Medicine at
the University of Michigan Medical Center.  He is a board specialist in
Internal Medicine and Pulmonary Diseases, and has been in practice since
1982.  Dr. Bria is responsible for the selection, design, and
implementation of clinical information systems, and has developed an
Applied Medical Informatics curriculum for residents and medical students
at the University of Michigan Medical Center.<P>

Dr. Bria is a Fellow in the American College of Chest Physicians, a member
of the Special Advisory Panel of Healthcare Information Management Systems
Society, and a member of the American Thoracic Society.  He is a consultant
to the Institute of Medicine on the Computerized Patient Record and to the
U.S. Congress on Healthcare Information Systems.  Dr. Bria is past
President of the Medical Information Systems Physicians Association.
<HR>
