<HEAD>
<TITLE>Jocelyn Dewitt</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="EEEEEE">

<B> <IMG hspace=3 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"><A HREF="/">Home</A> | <A HREF="./">Up</A> | <A HREF="/web/tools/">Tools</A> | <A HREF="/web/help/">Help</A> | <A HREF="/web/scripts/comment.acgi">Send a comment</A></B>
<HR>
<H2>Jocelyn DeWitt</H2>
<P>
 Director for User Relations for Medical Center Information Technology.
<P>
   Jocelyn G DeWitt, Ph.D. received her doctorate in public policy analysis 
from the University of Illinois.  For the past five years she has directed 
the development and implementation of the UMMC M NET project, a referring 
physician computer network that  links almost 2000 physicians across the 
state with the Medical Center.  For the past 18 months she has also directed 
the Medical Center's community health information network project, including 
the development of the proposal and negotiations with potential network 
partners and vendors.  She has just assumed the position of Director for 
User Relations for Medical Center Information Technology.

