<TITLE>Strategy for Physician Partnership</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="EEEEEE">

<B> <IMG hspace=3 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"><A HREF="/">Home</A> | <A HREF="./">Up</A> | <A HREF="/web/tools/">Tools</A> | <A HREF="/web/help/">Help</A> | <A HREF="/web/scripts/comment.acgi">Send a comment</A></B>
<HR><H1>Physician Network System for Partnership</H1>

<HR>
<H2>Michigan Network Provider Services Organization: a Info
System-intensive Strategy for Physician Partnership.</H2>
by Jack Billi
<P>
Physicians across Michigan and the US have formed into physician organizations to improve their practice, measure and improve quality, consolidate high cost administrative functions, increase economic leverage and become ready to thrive under prepaid capitated managed care (HMOs, etc.).  Most of these POs are undercapitalized, understaffed and have inadequate information system infrastructure.  The options available to solve these problems are to partner with their local hospital, to partner with a for-profit physician management company (PhyCor, Coastal), or to join together in a community owned consortium/cooperative model. The university is evaluating the formation of such a model.   
<HR>
Return to the <A HREF="./">Lecture Series</A> table


