<H2>HL-7 </H2>

by Mary Kratz
<P>
HL-7 (Health Level 7)For further HL7 details, you could link to the following URLs:
<P>
Interchange incentives at UMMC.  

Existing UMMC applications and databases store enterprise data in
proprietary and highly customized data representations.  These proprietary
and customized formats make access and integration of UMMC information both
expensive and time consuming.  Inconsistencies in the data definitions
require current interfaces and databases undergo extensive site-specific
programming and maintenance.  The first steps toward making information
available begins with mapping the content of existing applications internal
databases onto a Standard structure.  This mapping provides a framework for
both new and old applications to communicate within the UMMC enterprise.
This framework can minimizing incompatibility and maximize the exchange of
information among systems if each system has a common data model to work from.  

Health Level Seven (HL7) is Standards organization for electronic data
exchange in healthcare environments, with a special emphasis on inpatient
acute care facilities (i.e., hospitals).  All current projects for data
exchange, on the Application Interface Engine at UMMC, will be in an HL7
format. 

The discussion on 2/14/96 will be a basic overview of the HL7 organization,
an explanation of the abstract messaging syntax of HL7 and where to go for
further information on HL7.


<UL>
<LI>http://spwww.mcit.med.umich.edu/projects/mshl7web/main.html
<LI>Duke University Gopher and Web
     Gopher: dumccss.mc.duke.edu [152.3.78.2]<BR>
<LI>     WWW: http://www/mc.duke.edu/ftp/standards.html<BR>
<LI>     http://dumccss.mc.duke.edu/ftp/standards/html
<LI>Columbia University FTP server for HL7 source code
     cucis.cis.columbia.edu [128.59.160.100]

</UL>


</P>

