<TITLE>Information Technology at UMMC</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="EEEEEE">
<B> <IMG hspace=3 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"><A HREF="/">Home</A> | <A HREF="./">Up</A> | <A HREF="/web/tools/">Tools</A> | <A HREF="/web/help/">Help</A> | <A HREF="/web/scripts/comment.acgi">Send a comment</A></B>
<HR>

<H2>Information Technology at UMMC </H2>

<B>by M.McGill</B>
<P>
 I propose to discuss the evolution and directions of the
Information Technology activities at UMMC.  After a little historical
background on the state of Information Technology at UMMC in 1992 and bring
it forward to today.   The meat of the presentation will be to project the
strategies for our IT activities and how we can achieve these strategies.
The topics will include the inter-relationships between departmental
systems and central systems, the responsibilities associated with systems,
information, and using information in a distributed environment.<BR>

I'll be talking about some of the business changes that drive information
needs in Medical Centers and specific projects underway at UMMC.

</UL>
McGill is a Fellow of the American Society for the Advancement of Science.

      

</UL>
