<HR>
<H2>Carl Zang</H2>
<P>

I am currently employed in MCIT as an Adviser for Computer Information
Systems, and have worked at the Hospital for the past 21 years.  I've
worked as a supervisor, manager, financial systems coordinator, and
technical consultant over that time in Hospital administration,
finance and now in MCIT. 
<P>
I became involved with computer systems
about 12 years ago and have been directly or indirectly involved with
most of the systems development related to the financial transaction
and reporting systems on the mainframe and in the client/server
environments. 
<P> 
I am involved in the Data Access project on Campus
through my association with the Procurement Model and its related
education development group.  I am also involved in the asset
management planning group with the PeopleSoft project currently being
planned for implementation at UofM.


