<HEAD>
<TITLE>Electronic medical records</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="EEEEEE">
<B> <IMG hspace=3 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"><A HREF="/">Home</A> | <A HREF="./">Up</A> | <A HREF="/web/tools/">Tools</A> | <A HREF="/web/help/">Help</A> | <A HREF="/web/scripts/comment.acgi">Send a comment</A></B>

<HR>

<H2>Confidentiality and The Electronic Medical Record</H2>
by Sean Auton <P> 


This lecture will show how the traditional medical records rules and regulations can be applied in an  electronic environment.  
<P>
This will include the changing scope of security 
and the added potential that electronic information can provide. 

<P>
 As 
with the previous lecture, we'd like to reserve some time at the end to 
address specific questions/issues that the group has.



