<TITLE>Dr.-Ing. Klaus-Peter Beier</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="EEEEEE">

<B> <IMG hspace=3 SRC= "/web/images/dot_clear.gif"><A HREF="/">Home</A> | <A HREF="./">Up</A> | <A HREF="/web/tools/">Tools</A> | <A HREF="/web/help/">Help</A> | <A HREF="/web/scripts/comment.acgi">Send a comment</A></B>
<HR>
<H2>Dr.-Ing. Klaus-Peter Beier</H2>
<P>
Dr.-Ing. Klaus-Peter Beier
Director, University of Michigan Virtual Reality Laboratory
Associate Professor & Research Scientist
<P>
Dr.Beir received his Ph.D. from the Technical University of Berlin, Germany, in the
combined areas of naval architecture and computer science. He joined the
faculty at the University of Michigan in Ann Arbor in 1984. 
<P>
His areas of
research include CAD/CAM, free-form surface design, computer graphics, and
scientific visualization.
<P> In cooperation with the automotive industry,
Professor Beier developed several research laboratories at the University
of Michigan including the Virtual Reality Laboratory, a facility that is
widely recognized for its pioneering work in research and development of
industrial applications of virtual environments.
<P>

 Director for User Relations for Medical Center Information Technology.
<P>
