<HEAD><TITLE>Annual Meeting</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#EEFFFF">
<H2>PSI Annual Meeting</H2>
<P>
<B>Introduction: Global Technology</B>
<P>
<B>By Milton Huang M.D.</B><P>

<P>Advances in information technology are rapidly changing all aspects of how we communicate.  Tools and techniques like videoconferencing, the World Wide Web, interactive multimedia, etc.  are making communications not only faster and farther, but also changing qualitative aspects of communication as well.  
<P>How we communicate and what we communicate shift as we take advantage of such new information tools.

<P>In this introduction to symposium I, I will give a broad overview of some of the new technologies that are now available and that are beginning to be employed to assist in psychiatric work.  
<P>I hope to illustrate some of these technologies and indicate some of the potential future applications wecan develop in our field.


<P>
<A HREF="/web/psi/mtg/">Return to Annual Meeting</A>





