<HEAD><TITLE>levebre.B</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#EEFFFF">
<H2>PSI Annual Meeting</H2>
<P>
<B>By Arlette Lefebvre M.D..</B><P>
<B> Ability OnLine:</B> A Telecommunications Network for Disabled Children
and Adolescents and Innovative Prevention Project.

<P>

Arlette Lefebvre, MD (and staff psychiatrist at the Hospital for Sick
Children, in Toronto) and Brian Hillis, computer consultant and
System Manager of Ability OnLine.
<P>
Ability OnLine is the name of a Telecommunications Network which was
created for youngsters with disabilities or chrnic illness. The main
objective of this one-of-a-kind, primary prevention program is to put
children and adolescents with disabilities in touch with the world,
electronically, right from their hospital bed, home or school.
<P>
Disabled and chronically ill youngsters are twice as likely to suffer
from psychological adjustment problems and psychiatric disorders than
their healthy peers.
<P> They are also ten times more likely to drop out
of school before completing their secondary education, to have less
leisure activities and a more restricted social life, and to become
either unemployed or underemployed  during their adult years, and
this, despite concerted efforts on the part of health and education
systems to promote their full integration into the mainstream of
society. 
<P>
This telecommunications network already links over 7,000 regular
users from accross Canada and receives an average of 1200 calls a
day.
<P>
 In this presentation, we will show you the principles upon which
we built this distinctive, friendly and family-oriented platform and
link disabled and non-disabled youngsters, parent, health
professionals and educators in a barrier-free world where appearance,
mobility, speech and social class do not matter and where health
information and mentors can be readily accessed anytime, from anywhere.
<P>
Our web page can be found at:
<P><A HREF=" http://www.ablelink.org">http://www.ablelink.org</A>



<P>
<HR>

<A HREF="/web/psi/mtg/">Return to Annual Meeting</A>





