<HEAD><TITLE>Annual Meeting</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#EEFFFF">
<H2>PSI Annual Meeting</H2>
<P>
<B>Business Process Reengineering
<P>
 By Sheila Marcus M.D.</B>
<P>
Market forces, including those of managed care are increasingly heightening physician's awareness of the "business of medicine" Patient satisfaction, outcomes, practice guidelines,  and efficiency are medical buzzwords of the 90's.
<P>
 Historically, medicine had been shielded from market competition, occupying the comfortable niche market under fee-for-service  payers. 
<P>
Business Process Reengineering is a term coined to describe the redesign of business processes to achieve dramatic improvements in critical, contemporary measures of performance, such as cost, quality, service and speed. 
<P>The fundamental features of BPR as well as their relationship to psychiatric practice will be explored in this portion of the seminar. In addition the important relationship of BPR to information technology will be underlined. 
<P>
Physicians who wish to maintain and improve their competitive edge in the more rigorous modern marketplace will find these tools invaluable in their practice. 

<P>
<A HREF="/web/psi/mtg/">Return to Annual Meeting</A>





