<H1><A NAME="newsletter">The Interpsych Newsletter</A></H1>
IPN (ISSN#1355-2562) is a monthly, electronic publication of InterPsych that contains articles on current events in mental health, updates from InterPsych and its electronic forums, as well as original research and theoretical articles. The newsletter also contains new mental health resources on the Internet and conference, employment, and announcement listings.
<P>
IPN is now also <A HREF="http://www1.mhv.net/~grohol/ipnx.htm"><B>available through the World Wide Web</B></A> thanks to John Grohol.
<HR>
<B>To subscribe to the IPN</B>, please send a message to: LISTSERV@FRA.PSYCH.NEMC.ORG 
<P>
with the body of the message:
<P>
SUBSCRIBE IPN
<P>
Please note, you will NOT receive the Newsletter unless you subscribe using the procedure outlined above.  Additionally, this listservice will be a "send only" mailing list which means that the list will be used solely for the purpose of distributing the Newsletter. No other messages will be posted via this list.
<P>
<B>To unsubscribe from the IPN</B>, please send a message to: LISTSERV@FRA.PSYCH.NEMC.ORG 
<P>
with the body of the message:
<P>
UNSUBSCRIBE IPN
<HR>
If you are interested in <B>authoring an article</B>, please read the <A HREF="ipnauthr.htm">Instructions for Authors</A>.
<P>
For further information contact the Editor-in-Chief, Sean Sullivan
(<A HREF="mailto:ssulliva@opal.tufts.edu">ssulliva@opal.tufts.edu</A>)
<HR>
Return to <A HREF="./">InterPsych Index</A><P>
