<HR>
<STRONG>The usual method for <A NAME="register">registering</A> for a forum</STRONG> is via a single piece of e-mail.  
<P>
SEND E-MAIL TO the <A HREF="#servers">appropriate server</A><BR>

<P>
IN THE BODY OF THE E-MAIL TYPE:<BR>
Subscribe <A HREF="#slist">name-of-forum</A>
<HR>
<B>For example</B>, here's how Jane Doe subscribes to ASSESS (assessment-psychometrics):
<P>
SEND E-MAIL TO:<BR>
listserv@sjuvm.stjohns.edu
<P>
IN THE BODY OF THE E-MAIL TYPE<BR>
Subscribe ASSESS
<P>
<B>Another example</B>, here's how Jane Doe subscribes to affective-disorders:
<P>
SEND E-MAIL TO:<BR>
listserv@netcom.com
<P>
IN THE BODY OF THE E-MAIL TYPE<BR>
Subscribe affective-disorders
<HR>
<A NAME="servers"></A>If your web browser supports e-mailing, you can try to subscribe right now.  Just click on the server you want to send to, and type in the body of your message.<P>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="mailto:listserv@netcom.com">Netcom</A> = listserv@netcom.com
<LI><A HREF="mailto:listserv@sjuvm.stjohns.edu">SJU</A> = listserv@sjuvm.stjohns.edu
<LI><A HREF="mailto:listproc@sheffield.ac.uk">Sheffield</A> = listproc@sheffield.ac.uk
<LI><A HREF="mailto:majordomo@psycom.net">PsyCom</A> = majordomo@psycom.net
</UL>
<HR>
<B>If you are having problems</B> with subscribing or unsubscribing at Netcom, contact the "Vacation Peon" at <A HREF="mailto:vacation@netcom.com">vacation@netcom.com</A>.
<HR>
<B>Mailing a note to a forum</B> is different than sending an instruction to the Mailing list manager.  Simply address the note to 
<P>
<A HREF="#slist">name-of-forum</A>@servercomputer
<P>
<B>For example</B>, here's how Jane Doe sends a message to ASSESS:
<P>
SEND E-MAIL TO:<BR>
assess@sjuvm.stjohns.edu
<P>
IN THE BODY OF THE E-MAIL TYPE<BR>
whatever the message is
<P>
<B>Another example</B>, here's how Jane Doe sends a message to affective-disorders:
<P>
SEND E-MAIL TO:<BR>
affective-disorders@netcom.com
<P>
IN THE BODY OF THE E-MAIL TYPE<BR>
whatever the message is
<HR>
<B>Some forums require user-<A NAME="verify">verification</A></B>.  These are denoted by an asterisk (*) below on the short list of forums.
<P>
These other InterPsych forums are limited for use to mental health and behavioral science professionals, professional-oriented students, and special others only after user authentication via fax or e-mail.  I'm not sure, but I believe verification is the responsiblity of the list-owner.  InterPsych strives to encourage clear, and serious discourse over the Internet.  It has been learned from experience that some issues are best discussed in more limited groups.

<HR>
Tell me <A HREF="longlist.htm"><B>more about the forums</B></A> and list-owners<BR>
