<hr size=4>
<P>
<A NAME="archive"><font size=+3>T</font></A>he announcements of changes in Psychiatry Star that are sent out on the mailing list will also be archived at the website to maintain a record of our development.  The URL is <a href="/web/pstar/announce/">http://www.psych.med.umich.edu/web/pstar/announce/</a>
<P>

<A NAME="aacap"><font size=+3>T</font></A>he <a href="/web/aacap/">Homepage</a> of the AACAP has been recently reorganized, with a section on <a href="/web/aacap/contact.htm">"How to Contact the AACAP"</a> as they now have a set of e-mail accounts.  If you click on "Send a Comment" while looking at an AACAP web page, your comment will be automatically sent to them.  Clicking on "Send a Comment" while looking at another web page will send your message to the default webmaster account.
<P>

<A NAME="spanish"><font size=+3>F</font></A>acts for Families #1-29 have been translated into Spanish by the AACAP.  We now have the <a href="/web/aacap/apntsFam/">Spanish version</a> online, but we are still in the process of reviewing typos.
<P>

<A NAME="articles"><font size=+3>T</font></A>wo articles authored by <A href="/web/umpsych/staff/mhuang/">Milton Huang</A> and <A HREF="/web/umpsych/staff/nalessi/">Norm Alessi</A> were recently published in the August 1995 Psychiatric Times.  They are on the topics of the Web and the Psychiatric Informatics Fellowship.  We have been given permission to reproduce them electronically, and they are available at:
<ul>
<li><a href="/web/psytimes/psychwww.htm">http://www.psych.med.umich.edu/web/psytimes/psychwww.htm</a>
 <li><a href="/web/psytimes/infofelw.htm">http://www.psych.med.umich.edu/web/psytimes/infofelw.htm</a>
</ul>
<P>

<A NAME="links"><font size=+3>W</font></A>e are happy to add new links to:

<ul>
