<h1><IMG SRC="/web/images/pstaricn.gif" ALT="PsychStar Logo" ALIGN=RIGHT>Announcements (4/4/96):
</h1>

<ul>
<li><A HREF="/web/aacap/"><B>American Academy of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry</B></A>
<UL>
<LI>The AACAP is now changing to integrate the web into their organization, anticipating a move of the Web server from PsychStar in Michigan to their home in Washington D.C.  We are sad to announce that have determined that they currently do not have the resources to answer email from the website, and have asked us to remove the "send a comment" and other email references.  Expect this change in the near future.
<LI>New and updated Legislative alerts are now available on the site.
<LI>Emmanuelle has again redesigned some of the interfaces, such as the Facts for Families index, trying to make them easier to use.
<LI>We have earned multiple awards such as the 3 star award and recognition as one of the best sites in the January issue of Internet World. 
</UL>

<li> The University of Michigan Department of Psychiatry is also reorganizing in order to more effectively involve members in the web.  We hope to see resultant changes in the site soon.
<UL>
<LI>Our most recent change is the addition of a <A HREF="/web/UMpsych/announce/">News and Events Page</A> which lists some of the available lectures in the department and departmental news which Rosalie maintains.
</UL>


<li> The <A HREF="/web/psi/">Psychiatric Society for Informatics</A> has expanded its pages, including an announcement and description of its first annual meeting on May 4th in New York.

<LI> Milton's InterPsych page still exists although I haven't had much time to keep it updated with all the changes in the InterPsych organization.  As long as the forum leaders keep bugging me with email, and I will try to keep it up to date.

<LI>PsychStar
<UL>
<LI>Our sitehad 200,000 hits during the month of February!  
<LI>We have discovered intrinsic errors in our Send a Comment Script, but won't be fixing it in the near future.  Sorry if it is hard to send us mail.  
<LI>We've upgraded the memory in our PowerMacs to 16MB.  
</UL>


