<H3>Completed Publications in Scientific Journals (Peer Reviewed)</H3>

<ol>
 <li>Robbins, D.R., Alessi, N.E., Cook, S.C., Poznanski, E.O, and Yanchyshyn, G.W.:  The use of the research diagnostic criteria (RDC) for depression in adolescent psychiatric inpatients.  The Journal of the American Academy of Child Psychiatry, 1982; 21:251-255.

 <li>Robbins, D.R., Alessi, N.E., Yanchyshyn, G.W. and Colfer, M.V.:  Preliminary report on the dexamethasone suppression test in adolescents.  American Journal of Psychiatry, 1982; 139:942-943.

 <li>Alessi, N.E., Taylor, L. and Akil, H.:  Peptide F (pro-enkephalin fragment): Radioimmunoassay and stress-induced changes in adrenal.  Life Sciences, 1982; 31:1875-1878.

 <li>Robbins, D.R., Alessi, N.E., Yanchyshyn, G.W., and Colfer, M.V.:  The dexamethasone suppression test in psychiatrically hospitalized adolescents.  Journal of the American Academy of Child Psychiatry, 1983; 22:467-469.

 <li>Robbins, D.R., Alessi, N.E., Yanchyshyn, G.W. and Colfer, M.V.:  Psychodynamic and characterological heterogeneity among adolescents with major depressive disorders.  Journal of the American Academy of Child Psychiatry, 1983; 22,5:487-491.

 <li>Alessi, N.E., Khachaturian, H., Watson, S.J. and Akil, H.:  Postnatal ontogeny of acetylated and non-acetylated -endorphin in rat pituitary.  Life Sciences, Supplement I, 1983; 33:57-60.

 <li>Khachaturian, H., Alessi, N.E., Munfakh, N. and Watson, S.J.:  Ontogeny of opioid and related peptides in the rat CNS and pituitary:  An immunocytochemical study.  Life Sciences, Supplement I, 1983; 33:61-64.

 <li>Alessi, N.E., McManus, M., Brickman, A. and Grapentine, W.L.:  Suicidal behavior in serious juvenile offenders.  American Journal of Psychiatry, 1984; 141:286-287.

 <li>Alessi, N.E., McManus, M., Grapentine, W.L. and Brickman, A.:  The characterization of depressive disorders in serious juvenile offenders.  Journal of Affective Disorders, 1984; 6:9-17.

<li>Alessi, N.E. and Robbins, D.R.:  Symptoms and subtypes of depression among adolescents distinguished by the dexamethasone suppression test:  A preliminary report.  Psychiatry Research, 1984; 11:177-184.

<li>Brickman, A.S., McManus, M., Grapentine, W.L. and Alessi, N.E.:  Neuropsychological assessment of seriously delinquent adolescents.  Journal of the American Academy of Child Psychiatry, 1984; 23,4:453-457.

<li>McManus, M., Alessi, N.E., Grapentine, W.L. and Brickman, A.S.: Psychiatric disturbances in serious delinquents.  Journal of the American Academy of Child Psychiatry, 1984; 23,5:602-615.

<li>McManus, M., Brickman, A.S., Alessi, N.E. and Grapentine, W.L.:  Borderline personality in serious delinquents.  Comprehensive Psychiatry, 1984;  25:446-454.

<li>Robbins, D.R. and Alessi, N.E.:  Questions unanswered in article on DST in adolescents (Letter to the Editor).  American Journal of Psychiatry, 1984; 141,11:1492-1493.

<li>Robbins, D.R., Alessi, N.E., Colfer, M.V. and Yanchyshyn, G.W.:  Use of the Hamilton Rating Scale for Depression and the Carroll Self-rating Scale in adolescents.  Psychiatry Research, 1985; 14:123-129.

<li>Khachaturian, H., Alessi, N.E., Lewis, M.E., Munfakh, N., Fitzsimmons, M.D. and Watson, S.J.:  Development of hypothalamic opioid neurons:  A combined immunocytochemical and [3H]-thymidine autoradiographic study.  Neuropeptides, 1985; 5:477-480.

<li>Alessi, N.E and Khachaturian, H.:  Postnatal development of -endorphin immunoreactivity in the medulla oblongata of rat.  Neuropeptides, 1985; 5:473-476.

<li>Robbins, D.R. and Alessi, N.E.:  Suicide and the dexamethasone suppression test in adolescents.  Biological Psychiatry, 1985; 20(1):107-110.

<li>McManus, M., Brickman, A.S., Alessi, N.E. and Grapentine, W.L.:  Neurological dysfunction in serious delinquents.  Journal of the American Academy of Child Psychiatry, 1985; 24,4:481-486.

<li>Robbins, D.R. and Alessi, N.E.:  Depressive symptoms and suicidal behavior in adolescents.  American Journal of Psychiatry, 1985; 142:588-592.

<li>Khachaturian, H., Lewis, M.E., Alessi, N.E., and Watson, S.:  Time of origin of opioid peptide-containing neurons in the rat hypothalamus.  The Journal of Comparative Neurology, 1985; 236:538-546.

<li>Alessi, N.E. and Quinlan, P.:  Postnatal development of ACTH and -MSH in the medulla oblongata of rat:  -MSH is the predominant peptide.  Peptides, 1985; 6 (Suppl. 2):137-141.

<li>Dilsaver, S.C, Snider, R.M., and Alessi, N.E.:  Stress induces supersensitivity of a cholinergic system in rats.  Biological Psychiatry, 1986; 21:1093-1096.

<li>Dilsaver, S.C., Snider, R.M., Alessi, N.E.:  Amitriptyline supersensitizes a central cholinergic mechanism.  Biological Psychiatry, 1987; 22:459-507.

<li>Alessi, N.E., Robbins, D.R., and Dilsaver, S.C.:  Panic and depressive disorders among psychiatrically hospitalized adolescents.  Psychiatry Research, 1987; 20:275-283.

<li>Dilsaver, S.C., and Alessi, N.E.:  Chronic inescapable footshock produces cholinergic system supersensitivity.  Biological Psychiatry, 1987; 22:914-918.

<li>Dilsaver, S.C., Majchrzak, M. and Alessi, N.E.:  Chronic treatment with amitriptyline produces supersensitivity to nicotine.  Biological Psychiatry, 1988; 23:169-175.

<li>Alessi, N.E., Walden, M.E., and Hsieh, P.S.:  Nifedipine augments haloperidol in the treatment of Tourette's Syndrome.  Pediatric Neurology, 1988; 4:191.

<li>Dilsaver, S.C., and Alessi, N.E.:  Temperature as a dependent variable in the study of cholinergic mechanisms.  Progress in Neuropsychopharmacology and Biological Psychiatry, 1988; 12:1-32.

<li>Sholle-Martin, S. and Alessi, N.E.:  Adaptive functioning in children hospitalized for psychiatric disturbances.  Journal of the American Academy of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry, 1988; 27:636-641.

<li>Dilsaver, S.C., and Alessi, N.E.:  Antipsychotic withdrawal symptoms:  Phenomenology and pathophysiology.  Acta Psychiatrica Scandinavica, 1988; 77:241-246.

<li>Alessi, N.E., Quinlan, P., Khachaturian, H.:  MSG effects on beta-endorphin and alpha-MSH in the hypothalamus and caudal medulla.  Peptides, 1988; 9:689-695.

<li>Alessi, N.E. and Magen, J.:  Panic disorders identified among psychiatrically hospitalized children.  American Journal of Psychiatry, 1988; 145:1450-1452.

<li>Alessi, N.E. and Magen, J.:  Comorbidity of other psychiatric disturbances in depressed, psychiatrically hospitalized children.  American Journal of Psychiatry, 1988; 145:1582-1584.

<li>Alessi, N.E., Walden, M.E., and Hsieh, P.S.:  Nifedipine-haloperidol combination in the treatment of Tourette's syndrome:  A case study.  Journal of Clinical Psychiatry, 1989; 50:103-104.

<li>Dilsaver, S.C., Votolato, N.A., and Alessi, N.E..  Complications of phenylpropanolamine.  American Family Physician, 1989; 39:201-206.

<li>Naylor, M.W. and Alessi, N.E.:  Pseudo-ASA deficiency in an adolescent boy.  The Journal of the American Academy of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry, 1989; 28:444-449.

<li>Alessi, N.E., Krahn, D., Brehm, D., and Wittekindt, J.:  Case Report:  Prepubertal anorexia nervosa and major depressive disorder.  Journal of the American Academy of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry, 1989; 28:380-384.

<li>Robbins, D.R., Alessi, N.E., and Colfer, M.V.:  Treatment of adolescents with major depression:  implications of the DST and the melancholic clinical subtype.  Journal of Affective Disorders, 1989; 17:99-104.

<li>Alessi, N.E. and Sholle-Martin, S.:  Adaptive functioning at home and in the classroom (Letter to the Editor).  Journal of the American Academy of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry, 1989; 28:621-623.

<li>Alessi, N.E.:  The psychiatric trainee as an executive in training (Letter to the Editor).  American Journal of Psychiatry, 1989; 146:1518.

<li>Shain, B.N., Naylor, M. and Alessi, N.E.:  Comparison of self-rated and clinician-rated measures of depression in adolescents.  American Journal of Psychiatry, 1990; 147:793-795.

<li>Naylor, M., Greden, J., and Alessi, N.E.:  Plasma dexamethasone levels in children given the Dexamethasone Suppression Test.  Biological Psychiatry, 1990; 27:592-600.

<li>Shain, B.N., Shipley, J.E., Alessi, N.E. and Naylor, M.:  Imipramine effects on sleep in depressed adolescents:  A preliminary report.  Biological Psychiatry, 1990; 28:459-462.

<li>Sholle-Martin, S. and Alessi, N.E.:  Formulating a role for occupational therapy in child psychiatry:  A clinical application.  The American Journal of Occupational Therapy, 1990; 44:871-882.

<li>Dilsaver, S.C., Majchrzak, M.J., Alessi, N.E.:  Telemetric measurement of core temperature in psychobiological research:  Reliability and validation.  Progress in Neuropsychopharmacology and Biological Psychiatry, 1990; 14:591-596.

<li>Shain, B.N., King, C., Naylor, M., and Alessi, N.E.:  Chronic depression and hospital course in adolescents.  Journal of the American Academy of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry , 1991; 30:428-433.

<li>Alessi, N. and Bos, T.  Buspirone augmentation of fluoxetine in a child with treatment resistant OCD (Letter).  American Journal of Psychiatry , 1991; 148:1605-1606.

<li>Quinlan, P.E. and Alessi, N.E.:  Characterization of beta-endorphin-related peptides in the caudal medulla oblongata and hypothalamus of the prenatal, postnatal and adult rat.  Developmental Brain Research, 1992; 62:1-5.

<li>Abelson, J. and Alessi, N.:  Panic disorders--A Commentary.  Journal of the American Academy of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry, 1992; 31:114-116.

<li>Alessi, N., Knight, C., Eisner, S., and Bergs, J.:  A double-blind, placebo-controlled study of the effect of imipramine on TRH-induced urinary urgency in healthy males.  Psychoneuroendocrinology, 1992; 17:1-7.

<li>Shipley, J.E., Alessi, N.E., Wade, S., Haegele, A., and Helmbold, B.  Utility of an oral diffusion sink  (ODS) device for quantification of saliva corticosteroids in human subjects.  Journal of Endocrinology and Metabolism, 1992; 74:698-700.

<li>Ghaziuddin, N. and Alessi, N.E.:  An open clinical trial of trazodone in aggressive children. Journal of Child and Adolescent Psychopharmacology, 1992; 2: 291-297.

<li>Ghaziuddin, M., Tsai, L. and Alessi, N.:  ADHD and PDD (Letter).  Journal of American Academy of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry, 1992; 31:567.

<li>Zubieta, J., Alessi, N.:  Acute and crhonic administration of trazodone in the treatment of disruptive behavior disorders in children.  Journal of Clinical Psychopharmacology, 1992; 12:346-351.

<li>Alessi, N.:  A case for medical informatics in child and adolescent psychiatry (Letter).  Newsletter for American Academy of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry (in press).

<li>Alessi, N.:  Two week psychiatric hospitalization for children and adolescents are useless.  Negative (debate).  Journal of the American Academy of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry, 1993; 32:215-220.

<li>Ghaziuddin, M., Sheldon, S., Tsai, L.Y., and Alessi, N.E.:  Abnormalities of chromosome 18 in a girl with mental retardation and autistic disorder.  Journal of Intellectual Disability Research, 1993; 37:313-317.

<li>Ghaziuddin, M., Tsai, L.Y., Ghaziuddin, N., Eilers, L., Naylor, M. and Alessi, N.E.:  Utility of the head CT scan in child and adolescent psychiatry.  Journal of the American Academy of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry, 1993; 32:123-126.

<li>Zubieta, J., Alessi, N.:  Serotonin and its potential role in disruptive behavior disorder:  A critical literature review.  Journal of Child and Adolescent Psychopharmacology, 1993; 3:11-35.

<li>Ghaziuddin, M., Bolyard, B. and Alessi, N.  Autistic disorder in Noonan syndrome.  Journal of Intellectual Disability Research, 1993; 38: 67-72.

<li>Alessi, N.E.  Debate:  Effects of watching violence.  Journal of the American Academy of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry, 1992; 31: 988-989.

<li>Alessi, N.  Two week psychiatric hospitalization for children and adolescents are useless (response).  Journal of the American Academy of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry, 1993; 32:219-220.

<li>Alessi, N.E. and Schoof Kaufman, K:  The University of Michigan Child and Adolescent Mood Disorder Program.  Journal of Emotional and Behavioral Problems, 1993; 2:27-33.

<li>Alessi, N.:  Hope for the helpers:  Beyond therapeutic nihilism.  Journal of Emotional and Behavioral Problems, 1993; 2:39-41.

<li>Alessi, N.E.:  Guest editorial:  Depression in children and youth.  Journal of Emotional and Behavioral Problems, 1993; 2:3-4.

<li>Alessi, N.E.:  Despair at any age.  Journal of Emotional and Behavioral Problems, 1993; 2:13-17.

<li>Alessi, N. , Naylor, M., Ghaziuddin, M., and Zubieta, J.K.:  An update on lithium carbonate in children and adolescents.  Journal of the American Academy of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry, 1994; 33:291-304.

<li>Lauer, R.E., Giordani, B., Boivin, M.J., Halle, N., Glasgow, B., Alessi, N.E., and Berent, S.  The effects of depression on memory performance and metamemory in children.  Journal of the American Academy of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry, 1994; 33:5 679-685.

<li>Alessi, N., Cortes, J. and Hottois, M.  ADHD and the thyroid controversy (Letter).  Journal of the American Academy of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry, 1994; 33:756-757.

<li>Hunt, R.D., Hoehn, R., Narion, R., and Alessi, N..  Computer application for psychiatry.  Psychiatric Times, 1994; 11:33-36.

<li>Ghaziuddin, M., Alessi, N.E., and Greden, J.  Depression in children with autism/pervasive developmental disorder:  Presentation, family history and life events.  Journal of the American Academy of Child and Adolescent Psychiatry (submitted).
</ol>

